## ðŸ“˜ Section 4 â€“ Enabling Bedrock Logging

By default, Bedrock does not stream invocation data â€” and thatâ€™s where your leadership in system enablement begins.

After your CloudFormation stack deploys, grab the **CWLogsRoleArn** and **LogGroupName** from the stack **Outputs**, then run:

```bash
aws bedrock put-model-invocation-logging-configuration \
  --region <your-region> \
  --logging-config '{
    "cloudWatchConfig": {
      "logGroupName": "/aws/bedrock/model-invocations",
      "roleArn": "<CWLogsRoleArn>"
    },
    "textDataDeliveryEnabled": true,
    "imageDataDeliveryEnabled": false,
    "embeddingDataDeliveryEnabled": false
  }'

